# kriegerdataforge-cicd — Cursor Rules

## Purpose

This is a **shared reusable GitHub Actions workflow library**. Every workflow with
`on: workflow_call:` is a public API consumed by other KriegerDataForge repos:
`fitness-app-frontend`, `tiffanys-space`, `kriegerdataforge`, `arthurs-portfolio`,
`kriegerdataforge-terraform`. Treat all changes as potentially breaking for downstream
consumers.

## GitHub Actions

- Every externally-callable workflow MUST have `on: workflow_call:` as its trigger
  (add `on: workflow_dispatch:` alongside for manual testing only)
- Pin all third-party action versions to a commit SHA — never `@main` or `@latest`
- Never log secrets — even masked secrets should not appear in `echo` or debug steps
- Keep steps atomic — each step does one thing
- Prefer composite actions (`.github/actions/`) for logic reused across multiple workflows
- All production deployment jobs must use `environment:` for GitHub Environment protection gates

## Security

- Use `${{ secrets.NAME }}` for all credentials — never hardcode
- Set minimum required permissions on every workflow using the `permissions:` block
- Never use `pull_request_target` with an untrusted code checkout
- Use GitHub Environments for all production gates

## Backward Compatibility

- Adding a `required: true` input is a **breaking change** for all consumers —
  use `required: false` with a sensible `default:`, or coordinate with all consuming repos first
- Removing or renaming `outputs:` is a breaking change
- Changing `secrets:` requirements without updating all callers will silently break pipelines
- When in doubt, add a new workflow rather than modifying an existing one

## Repo Structure

- `.github/workflows/` — reusable workflows (all have `workflow_call:` trigger)
- `.github/actions/` — composite actions
- `scripts/` — shell helpers called by workflows
- `docs/` — workflow catalog and consumer integration guides

See `CLAUDE.md` for full project context and critical rules.
